The paper deals with evaluating the secrecy performance of a cooperative network, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also considers the wiretapping attack, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of network coding technique is proposed to improve the error performance and secrecy, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI).
